"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671789","Department of Health","false","2017-01-16","<p>Decisions on NHS Protect funding and development or continuation of NHS Protect sections are made on an annual basis. No specific assessment of these has been carried out. Annual NHS Protect plans and reports are available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/3647.aspx" target="_blank">www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/3647.aspx</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-16T16:20:28.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671789/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671789/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671789/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","NHS Protect","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he has made an assessment of the effect of the (a) change in the level of funding to NHS Protect and (b) removal of its legal protection unit on the performance of NHS Protect.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","59699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671790","Department of Health","false","2017-01-19","<p>The information is not collected centrally by the Department.</p><p> </p><p>Skills for Care, the partner in the sector skills council for social care, in England, collects data on the nationality of the adult social care workforce. The attached table adult social care workforce nationality contains estimated information on the number of direct care roles by nationality.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-19T11:28:26.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671790/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671790/answer","PQ59582 attached document.xlsx","PQ59582 attached file","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671790/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","Social Services: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many social care workers there are by nationality.","false","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","59582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671791","Department of Health","false","2017-01-19","<p>NHS England publishes data on the number of cancelled elective operations each quarter. Quarter 3, which includes December 2016, will be published on 10 February 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The data will be available via this link:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/cancelled-elective-operations/cancelled-ops-data/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/cancelled-elective-operations/cancelled-ops-data/</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-19T14:21:41.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671791/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671791/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many surgical procedures were cancelled in each NHS acute hospital trust in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","59598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671792","Department of Health","false","2017-01-19","<p>NHS England publish data on the performance of ambulance trusts. The latest data is for November 2016 and is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/</a></p><p> </p><p>Data for December 2016 will be available on 9 February 2017.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-19T14:20:08.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671792/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671792/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671792/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","Ambulance Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS ambulance trusts met their response targets in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","59599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671793","Department of Health","false","2017-01-16","<p>NHS England publish the monthly performance of all National Health Service trusts against the accident and emergency target. The latest data is for November 2016 and is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ae-waiting-times-and-activity/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ae-waiting-times-and-activity/</a></p><p>Data for December 2016 will be available on 9 February 2017.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-16T17:30:54.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671793/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671793/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671793/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS hospital trusts met the four-hour accident and emergency target in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","59596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671794","Department of Health","false","2017-01-16","<p>In November 2016 there were 39,457 hospital bed days where discharge was delayed whilst patients were awaiting a care package in their own home, and 4,352 whilst patients were awaiting community equipment and adaptations. These delays are estimated nationally to have affected 1.2% and 0.1% of hospital beds respectively.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-16T16:59:23.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671794/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671794/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671794/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many hospital beds in each hospital in England were being occupied by patients who were ready to be discharged but could not be released because a care package or support had not been put in place within the community on the most recent date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","59597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671795","Department of Health","false","2017-01-19","<p>Information for the latest available 12 month period is given in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>Net Ingredient Cost (NIC) of inhaled-medication prescription items written in the United Kingdom and dispensed in the community in England, classified as inhaled nebuliser products within British National Formulary sections 3.1.2 <em>Antimuscarinic bronchodilators</em>, 3.1.4 <em>Compound bronchodilator preparations </em>, 3.2 <em>Corticosteroids</em>, and 3.3.1 <em>Cromoglicate and related therapies</em></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Period</p></td><td colspan="3"><p>NIC £000’s</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Quarter</p></td><td><p>Non-branded <sup>1</sup></p></td><td><p>Branded <sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>20,959.2</p></td><td><p>246,653.5</p></td><td><p>267,612.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>25,205.7</p></td><td><p>226,611.2</p></td><td><p>251,816.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>25,390.8</p></td><td><p>231,223.2</p></td><td><p>256,614.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>25,047.6</p></td><td><p>228,186.1</p></td><td><p>253,233.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total <sup>3</sup></p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>96,603.3</p></td><td><p>932,674.1</p></td><td><p>1,029,277.3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Prescription Cost Analysis (PCA) system data provided by NHS Digital</p><p>Notes:</p><p><sup>1 </sup>Non-Branded are those drugs prescribed and available generically.</p><p><sup>2 </sup>Branded will include those generics that have been dispensed with a Brand name.</p><p><sup>3 </sup>Total figure may not sum due to rounding.</p><p> </p><p>Most inhaled products are licensed with a brand name, so even after the brand originator loses the patent exclusivity and alternative products become available, they usually will have a brand name, therefore their Net Ingredient Cost will be reported against branded spend.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-19T11:38:48.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671795/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671795/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671795/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","NHS: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the cost to the NHS of (a) branded and (b) non-branded inhaled medication in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Stephen McPartland","Stevenage","Stephen McPartland","59619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671796","Department of Health","false","2017-01-19","<p>The draft consultation has been developed by officials in the Department taking into account evidence from independent bodies, including the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence, and the House of Lords Science and Technology Committee. We will be seeking views of interested parties through the consultation process.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-19T14:26:19.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671796/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671796/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671796/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-11","Homeopathy: Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 13 December 2016 to Question 56390, and the Answer of 11 January 2017 to Question 58288, who he has sought advice from in preparing the draft consultation document and impact assessment that are being drafted for the consultation on homeopathy announced in November 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","59620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671797","Home Office","false","2017-01-17","<p>The Home Office publishes figures on the outcome of asylum claims made during each calendar year in table as_06 of the <em>Immigration Statistics</em> release.</p><p>The Home Office also publishes figures on asylum appeals and determinations, in table as_14_q of the quarterly <em>Immigration Statistics</em> release.</p><p>A copy of the latest release, <em>Immigration Statistics July to September 2016,</em> is available from <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/home-office/series/immigration-statistics-quarterly-release" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/home-office/series/immigration-statistics-quarterly-release</a></p><p>In addition, as part of its Transparency agenda the Home Office publishes data on decisions made within 6 months. Figures for the financial year 2015/16 can be found at tab Asy 01 at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asylum-transparency-data-november-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asylum-transparency-data-november-2016</a></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-17T17:54:38.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671797/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671797/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum claims in 2015 were (a) refused within six months of being lodged and (b) subsequently granted on appeal.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","59646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671798","Home Office","false","2017-01-19","<p>The asylum seeker accommodation contracts require providers to liaise and consult with local authorities prior to accommodating asylum seekers in any address, to ensure that accommodation provided to asylum seekers does not adversely affect local authority developments or community plans.</p><p>Any accommodation used as Housing of Multiple Occupancy must, prior to use demonstrate or seek relevant planning consents in line with housing regulations. Providers must also take into account the cultural compatibility of the environment; capacity of local health, education and other support services; concentration of accommodation of service users within particular areas; and the assessment of social tension risks. Once an initial accommodation centre is operational we do not routinely comment on its location.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-19T08:13:36.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671798/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671798/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671798/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Asylum: Hostels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 19 December 2016 to Question 57440, how the safety of asylum seekers housed in initial accommodation centres is protected when such centres go through public consultations and the planning process.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","59600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671799","Home Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>Only two of the 968 institutions that had their Tier 4 sponsor licences revoked between May 2010 and September 2016 were UK universities.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-13T10:21:30.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671799/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671799/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Overseas Students: Entry Clearances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 9 January 2017 to Question 58285, how many of the 968 institutions that had Tier 4 sponsor status revoked in the period May 2010 to September 2016 were universities.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","59615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671800","Home Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>I am sorry but in order to obtain these figures a manual interrogation of Home Office databases would need to be undertaken, which would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-13T10:26:32.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671800/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671800/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Overseas Students: Entry Clearances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 9 January 2017 to Question 58285, how many institutions failed their basic competence assessment but retained their licences after having had discretion applied in the period May 2010 to September 2016; and how many of those institutions were universities.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","59616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671801","Home Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Right to Rent scheme is predicated on checks being carried out by third parties (landlords and lettings agents). This means that the majority of illegal migrant prospective tenants will be denied access to the private rented sector as a result of these checks with no intervention by enforcement officers and no reference to the Home Office.</p><p>However, information about a range of factors is collected to measure the performance of the scheme itself. The Right to Rent scheme is a single measure among others which restrict access to services and benefits and encourage illegal migrants to return home.</p><p>Monitoring of the effects of the Right to Rent scheme on landlords and tenants is also ongoing through the expert Landlords Consultative Panel, co-chaired by the Immigration Minister and Lord Best, an acknowledged expert in the fields of housing and planning. The Panel comprises bodies representing landlords, lettings agents, housing charities, local authorities and the Equality and Human Rights Commission amongst others. The Panel meets periodically, and communication channels outside these meetings allow for reporting by private rented sector and third sector groups of the experience of those they represent.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-13T14:56:00.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671801/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671801/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Undocumented Migrants: Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to (a) measure and (b) assess the effects of the right to rent scheme.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","59523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671802","Home Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Government will not comment on the progress of this recruitment process while it is ongoing, but will provide information about the number of applications when the appointment is announced in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-13T12:33:28.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671802/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671802/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Metropolitan Police: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have applied for the post of Metropolitan Police Commissioner; and when the closing date is for applications for that post.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","59527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671803","Home Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Home Office is undertaking a process of engagement with the policing sector and independent experts on reform of the Police Core Grant Distribution Formula. No decisions will be taken until Ministers have considered the outcome of the Review. Any new formula will be subject to public consultation before implementation.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-13T12:34:44.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671803/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671803/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671803/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to publish the police funding formula.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","59528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671804","Home Office","false","2017-01-19","<p>We do not hold the requested data, in the requested format.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-19T17:17:46.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671804/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671804/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Marriage of Convenience: Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people were deported from the UK as a result of being involved in a sham marriage in (a) 2015 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","59525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671805","Home Office","false","2017-01-19","<p>The data requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-19T13:50:44.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671805/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671805/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671805/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been identified as potential victims of modern slavery or trafficking as a result of Operation Magnify; and how many of those people have been detained due to lack of documentation.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","59506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671806","Home Office","false","2017-01-17","<p>As part of the Government transparency agenda all year end and in-year bonuses are published in the Non-Consolidated Performance Related Pay (NCPRP) return. This information can be found on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-performance-related-pay-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">data.gov.uk</a>. The latest set of this information was published in March 2016 and relates to the 2014/15 performance year.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-17T14:08:48.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671806/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671806/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671806/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-11","Home Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many civil servants in her Department received a bonus in 2016; and what the total amount of such bonuses was at each grade in her Department in that year.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","59532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671807","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-18","<p>The UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (UNOCHA) recently stated that during 2016 there was a serious deterioration in access to Gaza for humanitarian organisations, due to the increased rate of permit denials for humanitarian staff applying to enter Gaza. In the West Bank, humanitarian access continues to be hampered by movement and access restrictions, but we have not received reports that there has been a significant change in levels of access over the last year.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-18T17:08:43.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671807/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671807/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671807/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Gaza and West Bank: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the level of access available to humanitarian organisations operating in (a) Gaza and (b) the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","59569"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671809","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-18","<p>In September 2016, the Secretary of State for International Development, Priti Patel, chaired a high level international event to shine a spotlight on the crisis in Yemen. At the event, donors pledged over $100 million in new funding, including half from a new UK pledge. The UK Government is also matching public donations to the current Disaster Emergency Committee appeal for Yemen, which has so far raised £15 million, including £5 million from the UK Government.</p><p>This brings our total commitment to Yemen to over £100 million in humanitarian aid for 2016/17, making us the fourth largest donor. In both 2015 and 2016, UK aid helped over 1 million Yemenis with food, nutrition, water and medical supplies.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-18T17:04:43.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671809/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671809/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671809/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Yemen: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to increase humanitarian assistance to Yemen; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","59580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671810","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-18","<p>The Secretary of State’s full examination of DFID’s programme in the Occupied Palestinian Territories (OPTs) is an internal process intended to scrutinise current programming and make recommendations that will ensure maximum impact and value for money to the UK taxpayer. DFID regularly engages with human rights and economic development non-governmental organisations (NGOs) that receive indirect funding through our access to justice and private sector development programmes. Discussions with these NGOs inform DFID’s analysis of humanitarian and development needs in the OPTs, which forms the basis of our programming decisions.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-18T17:06:11.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671810/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671810/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671810/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Occupied Territories: Non-governmental Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions she has had with non-governmental organisations funded by her Department that promote human rights and economic development in the Occupied Palestinian Territories as part of her review of funding in that region.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","59584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671811","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-18","<p>The UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (UNOCHA) recently assessed that since April 2016 the pace of reconstruction of homes destroyed or damaged during the 2014 conflict has slowed due to increased restrictions on the entry of building materials into the Gaza Strip, prolonging the vulnerability of more than 10,000 families who are still displaced. UNOCHA also assessed that by November 2016, 39 percent of the 17,800 housing units destroyed or severely damaged in the 2014 conflict had been rebuilt.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-18T17:15:10.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671811/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671811/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671811/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Gaza: Reconstruction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the pace and number of home reconstructions in Gaza through the Gaza Reconstruction Mechanism.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","59585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671813","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-18","<p>The table attached details all development programmes greater than £5m that have been approved by DFID Ministers since July 2016.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-18T17:48:39.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671813/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671813/answer","59683.docx","59683","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671813/answer","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671813/answer/previousversion/30179","Biography information for Rory Stewart","20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Department for International Development: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what each item of expenditure over £5 million was that was authorised by Ministers of her Department in each of the last six months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","59683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671814","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-16","<p>Transfers between Department for International Development and Other Government Departments are set out in the Main Estimates and Supplementary Estimates.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-16T17:49:41.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671814/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671814/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671814/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Department for International Development: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what transfers were made from her Department's budget to other government departments in the last 18 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","59684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671815","Department for International Development","false","2017-01-16","<p>Information on the Department’s monthly spending is included in the HM Treasury publication ‘OSCAR in-year data release’. The most recent publication includes data up to September 2016, and is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/oscar-publishing-data-from-the-database-december-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/oscar-publishing-data-from-the-database-december-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>In addition, annual information is included in the Department’s Annual Report and Accounts, available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfid-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-16" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfid-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-16</a></p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-01-16T17:47:17.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671815/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671815/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671815/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-01-11","Department for International Development: Departmental Expenditure Limits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what her Department's (a) resource DEL and (b) capital DEL (i) budget and (ii) outturn was in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","59682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671816","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-23","<p>The Government is committed to honouring the Belfast Agreement, and we shall ensure our proposals for a Bill of Rights are compatible with it.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-01-23T11:07:46.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671816/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671816/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671816/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-11","Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent assessment she has made of the potential effect of repeal or reform of the Human Rights Act 1998 on the Belfast Agreement.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","59693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671817","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-19","<table><tbody><tr><td><p>Prohibiting those participating in court proceedings from obscuring their faces is a matter for the judiciary to decide upon on a case-by-case basis. The Government is satisfied with the operation of the current practice.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-01-19T14:06:42.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671817/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671817/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671817/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-11","Courts: Privacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether her Department has assessed the potential merits of prohibiting defendants, witnesses and others participating in court proceedings from obscuring their faces, except on medical grounds, or in circumstances where a trial anonymity order has been granted.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","59623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671818","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-15","<p>The procurement for the supplier of the new Electronic Monitoring Tags is ongoing and we expect to confirm the outcome in due course.</p><p>Since April 2016, the cost of procurement activity for the supplier of the new electronic monitoring tags has been £450,000.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-15T17:51:12.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671818/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671818/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671818/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-11","Electronic Tagging","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the Written Ministerial Statement of 25 February 2016, HCWS549, what progress her Department has made on procuring new electronic monitoring based on satellite tracking technology; and what the costs of that procurement process have been to date.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","59530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671819","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-23","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p>We are determined to improve the family justice response to vulnerable witnesses and victims of domestic abuse in particular. Family judges have a range of powers to make sure difficult courtroom situations are handled sensitively for vulnerable witnesses and we continue to work with the judiciary to consider what additional protections may be necessary.</p><p> </p><p>We are particularly concerned about the fact that unrepresented alleged perpetrators of abuse can directly cross-examine their alleged victims in family proceedings. The Lord Chancellor is urgently considering how to put an end to this practice.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-01-23T11:02:32.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671819/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671819/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671819/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-11","Family Courts: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many cases in the family courts involved domestic violence in each year from 2010 to 2016.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","59538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671820","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-23","<p>We are determined to improve the family justice response to vulnerable witnesses, and victims of domestic abuse in particular.</p><p> </p><p>Family judges have a range of powers to make sure difficult courtroom situations are handled sensitively for vulnerable witnesses, and we continue to work with the judiciary to consider what additional protections may be necessary.</p><p> </p><p>We are particularly concerned about the fact that unrepresented alleged perpetrators of abuse can directly cross-examine their alleged victims in family proceedings. The Lord Chancellor is urgently considering how to put an end to this practice.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-01-23T11:04:20.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671820/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671820/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671820/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-11","Courts: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will bring forward legislative proposals to prevent perpetrators of domestic violence from cross-examining in person the victims of that domestic violence and to ensure that contact between those perpetrators and those victims is prevented while they are within court buildings.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","59539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671821","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-23","<p>This data is published quarterly on gov.uk. The data as at 31 December 2016 is scheduled to be published on 26 January 2017.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-01-23T15:22:16.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671821/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671821/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671821/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-11","Prisoners: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many foreign nationals of which nationalities there were in prisons in England and Wales on 1 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","59524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671823","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-01-16","<p>This Government is strongly committed to tackling violence against women and girls in all its forms, and published a new ‘Ending Violence Against Women and Girls’ (VAWG) Strategy in March 2016, supported by increased funding of £80m to 2020.</p><p> </p><p>As Violence Against Women and Girls (VAWG) policy is devolved to Northern Ireland and Scotland, the strategy covers England and Wales only, but the Government will continue to work with counterparts in the NI Executive to share best practice. Officials from the Home Office and Ministry of Justice engage regularly with their counterparts in Northern Ireland on these issues.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-01-16T15:55:27.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671823/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671823/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671823/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-01-11","Domestic Abuse: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will meet the Northern Ireland Justice Minister to discuss how his Department can support work to prevent violence against women and children in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","59595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671824","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-16","<p>I have regular discussions with my Cabinet colleagues, including the Chancellor of the Exchequer, on a wide range of economic matters. The Chancellor has announced that HM Treasury will put in place arrangements to guarantee funding for structural and investment fund projects that were signed after the Autumn Statement 2016 up until the UK leaves the EU.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-16T15:41:54.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671824/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671824/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671824/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-01-11","EU Grants and Loans: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on Scotland's allocation of (a) the European Social Fund and (b) the European Regional Development Fund since the UK's decision to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Natalie McGarry","Glasgow East","Natalie McGarry","59696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671825","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-18","<p>Migrants from outside the UK and within the UK make a significant contribution to Scotland – not only in terms of its economy, but also society and wellbeing. This Government will always welcome the brightest and the best who come here to work.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-18T13:36:08.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671825/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671825/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671825/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-01-11","Immigration: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the effect of levels of immigration on Scotland's economic performance in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","59574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671826","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-18","<p>Section 29 of the Scotland Act 1998 sets out that the Scottish Parliament cannot legislate incompatibly with any of the rights in the European Convention on Human Rights. There are no plans to withdraw from the European Convention on Human Rights.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-18T13:37:03.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671826/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671826/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671826/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-01-11","European Convention on Human Rights: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the UK's signatory status to the European Convention on Human Rights on the competencies of the Scottish Parliament.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","59504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671827","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>Network Rail is delivering the Great Western Electrification Programme to the dates set out in the latest publication of their Enhancement Delivery plan. This includes completing electrification of the Great Western Mainline between London and Bristol Parkway by December 2018.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T14:49:34.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671827/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671827/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671827/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Great Western Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, by what date he expects the electrification of the rail line between London and Bristol to be completed.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","59547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671828","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Government Car Service currently operates 55 diesel cars out of 89 overall in the fleet.</p><p>The Government Car Service has for some time been reviewing their use of diesel cars and has introduced low emission and ultra-low emission vehicles to their fleet as diesel cars become due for replacement.</p><p> </p><p>Just this month five diesel cars are due for disposal and they are being replaced by petrol hybrid cars.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-16T17:09:10.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671828/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671828/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671828/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Government Car Service: Diesel Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many diesel cars there are in the Government Car Service.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","59558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671829","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Government will publish the London and South Coast Rail Corridor Study, and its response to the recommendations, in due course.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T14:15:07.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671829/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671829/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671829/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Railways: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 10 October 2016 to Question 46666, when he plans to publish the findings of the London and South Coast Rail Corridor Study.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","59698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671830","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>Analysis carried out for the government in 2015 suggested that insurance premiums are broadly equivalent between electric vehicles and their petrol or diesel equivalents.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-16T17:16:56.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671830/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671830/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671830/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the level of insurance costs for new ultra-low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","59695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671831","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-18","<p>The Department has received no such request.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-18T12:23:40.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671831/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671831/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671831/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Southern: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has received a request from Transport for London to fund extra bus services on days on which industrial action affects Southern rail services.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","59673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671832","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>We do not hold this information. The contractual requirement is to measure the amount of trains that run with fewer than the scheduled number of carriages during peak-time hours, not the whole day. And we do not disaggregate the figure to the constituent business groups (Gatwick Express, Great Northern, Southern and Thameslink), but measure performance across the entire franchise.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-16T14:07:12.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671832/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671832/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671832/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Southern: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Southern Rail services ran with fewer than their scheduled number of carriages in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","59594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671833","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>I am committed to building transport networks that work for everyone, including ensuring that disabled people have the same access to transport services as other members of society.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently developing best practice guidance in delivering disability awareness training. This has been informed by engagement with disabled people and the bus industry, and aims to ensure that bus drivers have the knowledge and skills to provide passengers with the appropriate assistance they need, including the use of ramps for wheelchair users.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T14:44:26.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671833/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671833/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671833/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Bus Services: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to improve disability awareness among bus drivers on the use of a ramp when required for disabled passengers.","false","Biography information for Will Quince","Colchester","Will Quince","59634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671834","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>Taxis and private hire vehicles (PHVs) provide a particularly important service for many disabled people, helping them to remain independent and to complete journeys which may not be possible using other forms of transport.</p><p> </p><p>I recognise that the availability of wheelchair accessible taxis and PHVs varies across Great Britain, particularly in rural areas. I know too, however, that they can sometimes be difficult to access for some ambulant disabled people. As such we encourage local licensing authorities to use their existing powers to ensure that a range of vehicle categories are represented in their taxi and PHV fleets. We have also introduced powers in the Deregulation Act 2015 to enable the sub-contracting of PHV services across local authority boundaries, helping to ensure that wheelchair accessible vehicles are available wherever they are required.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T14:39:51.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671834/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671834/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671834/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","Taxis: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that there is sufficient provision of accessible taxis for disabled people in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Will Quince","Colchester","Will Quince","59633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671835","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>An Alternative Dispute Resolution mechanism for the HS2 project will be in place by May, when land for the railway starts to be permanently compulsorily acquired.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T17:26:31.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671835/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671835/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made by HS2 Ltd on introducing an alternative dispute resolution for landowners relating to compensation.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","59643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671836","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Main Works Invitation to Tender documentation issued by HS2 Limited in 2016 included a requirement to appoint an Agricultural Liaison Officer for work undertaken in rural areas. The Contractor, when appointed in late 2017, will provide a dedicated Agricultural Liaison Officer service to address issues arising from landowners and farmers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-16T15:03:20.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671836/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671836/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671836/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-11","High Speed Two","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on when HS2 Ltd plans to appoint an agricultural liaison officer.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","59644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671837","Wales Office","false","2017-01-17","<p>The Wales Office remains in active discussions with colleagues across Whitehall to consider how the Government can best support S4C.</p><p>Since 1 January 2016 we have received significant levels of correspondence regarding the Government’s support to S4C. All letters have received a response. I take a close interest in all matters relating to S4C, including letters and emails, and answer as required.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-01-17T10:17:26.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671837/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671837/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671837/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-01-11","S4C","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many letters or emails his Department has received on Government support for S4C since 1 January 2016; and how many of those letters or emails he has personally (a) read and (b) replied to.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","59656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671838","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-16","<p>HM Revenue and Customs has 237 outstanding appeals against decisions made by Concentrix up to 16 January 2017.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-01-16T16:21:30.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671838/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671838/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671838/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-11","Concentrix","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many outstanding appeals against decisions made by Concentrix on tax credits there were up to 16 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","59681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671839","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-16","<p>Published Official Statistics showing number of starts to Work Choice by benefit claimed at referral can be accessed via the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-choice-statistics-number-of-starts-and-referrals--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-choice-statistics-number-of-starts-and-referrals--2</a></p><p>These statistics show that in the 12 months to September 2016 there were 11,450 starts to Work Choice of which 6,100 were on jobseeker’s allowance and 2,100 were on incapacity related benefits (employment and support allowance, incapacity benefit or severe disablement allowance). The additional breakdown by ESA phase is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-16T12:41:37.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671839/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671839/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671839/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Employment Schemes: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people are participating in the Work Choice programme; and how many of those participants are claiming (a) jobseeker's allowance, (b) employment and support allowance and are in the work-related activity group, and (c) employment and support allowance and are in the support group.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","59627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671840","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-16","<p>The latest published information shows that the average clearance time for all benefit appeals is 16 weeks.</p><p> </p><p>The Information in relation to the Mandatory Reconsideration part of the dispute process is not available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-16T15:09:53.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671840/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671840/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671840/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Personal Independence Payment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information his Department holds on the (a) average and (b) longest time between a claimant receiving a letter denying a claim for personal independence payment and the completion of a tribunal appeal hearing relating to that claim.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","59593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671841","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-17","<p>This information is published online and can be found at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-independence-payment-april-2013-to-october-2016" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-independence-payment-april-2013-to-october-2016</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-17T17:40:20.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671841/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671841/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671841/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Personal Independence Payment: Motability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants who have been transferred from disability living allowance to personal independence payment (PIP) have had their eligibility for the Motability scheme removed as a result of reassessment using the new PIP guidelines.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","59602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671842","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-19","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions does not have a system in place to monitor whether written correspondence is successfully delivered. However, the Department regularly checks with its customers that their addresses are current and takes immediate action to amend any records when notified of changes.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-01-19T15:38:36.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671842/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671842/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671842/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Department for Work and Pensions: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether his Department has a system for monitoring whether its written correspondence to claimants has been successfully delivered.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","59603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671843","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-19","<p>Only a small proportion, 7%, of all PIP decisions have been appealed.</p><p> </p><p>As part of on-going review and improvement analysis of PIP, we are continuing to make efforts to ensure that all decisions, whether made initially or at Mandatory Reconsideration, are the best informed decisions. For example, the department is running a series of trials which looks at the end to end PIP decision making process with a particular focus on MR and explores the different ways we can improve the quality of our decision making.</p><p> </p><p>However, it is important that claimants can appeal their award decision if they are unhappy with it. Moreover, a request for an appeal does not mean that the decisions taken initially and as part of Mandatory Reconsideration were not right. Claimants often provide new, relevant evidence at the tribunal stage.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-19T15:44:01.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671843/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671843/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671843/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Personal Independence Payment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to reduce the proportion of personal independence payment cases which are appealed at a tribunal.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","59604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671844","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-19","<p>As part of on-going review and improvement analysis of PIP, we are continuing to make efforts to ensure that our initial decisions are as well informed as they can be and of the highest standard. For example, the department is running a series of trials which looks at the end to end PIP decision making process with a particular focus on MR and explores the different ways we can improve the quality of our decision making.</p><p> </p><p>However, it is important that claimants can request a Mandatory Reconsideration if they are unhappy with the initial decision. Moreover, a request for a Mandatory Reconsideration does not mean the initial decision was not right. Claimants often provide new, relevant evidence at the tribunal stage.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-19T15:48:01.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671844/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671844/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671844/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans his Department has to reduce the number of personal independence payment mandatory reconsiderations.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","59605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671845","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-19","<p>During normal processing, Motability Operations are notified the day after the notification is issued to the claimant. There is a process in place to ensure the claimant is not contacted before they receive the decision notification.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-19T15:32:56.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671845/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671845/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671845/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Personal Independence Payment: Motability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether the Motability Operations teams are notified of a personal independence payment claimant's award status before the claimant themself is notified.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","59601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671846","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-19","<p>If a pensioner’s pre-1997 defined benefit pension rights include a Guaranteed Minimum Pension (GMP) earned after April 1988, that element must be increased by inflation, capped at 3 per cent.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Defined benefit pensions accrued after 1997 are subject to statutory limited price indexation: inflation capped at 5 per cent for pensions accrued between April 1997 and April 2005 and inflation caped at 2.5 per cent for pensions accrued after April 2005.</p><p> </p><p>We have no plans to change this.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-01-19T15:30:13.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671846/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671846/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671846/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will introduce a right to statutory inflation increases for defined pension schemes that have pre-1997 accrued rights.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","59552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671847","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-17","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions and the Department of Health have published ‘Improving Lives – the Work, Health and Disability Green Paper’. The Green Paper sets out the Government’s proposals for improving work and health outcomes for disabled people and people with long-term health conditions.</p><p> </p><p>Many employers are already creating healthy, inclusive workplaces, but more needs to be done so that employers provide the support needed for employees with disabilities and long-term health conditions, to help them get into and stay in work</p><p> </p><p>Through the Green Paper we are asking about the barriers preventing employers from recruiting and retaining disabled people and people with health conditions, and what measures would help them in doing so. Specifically:</p><p> </p><ul><li>We are consulting on reform to Statutory Sick Pay to support phased returns to work. A phased return to work can be beneficial to both employer and employee, as it may help prevent further periods of absence or the employee falling out of work entirely;</li><li>How we can transform occupational health provision to ensure it more closely meets the spectrum of need, including the needs of employers.</li><li>The Green Paper also announced a review of the current operation of the fit note. This review will look at the current system and whether it meets the needs of its users – including employers. We are seeking views to inform this review through the consultation.</li></ul>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-01-17T17:44:10.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671847/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671847/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671847/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-11","Occupational Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has for further measures to assist employers in supporting employees to return to work after a health-related absence.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","59500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671849","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-18","<p>BEIS and the Oil and Gas Authority are in regular contact with the Scottish Government and Scottish Enterprise. The Department is supportive of the Scottish Government on the Oil and Gas Decommissioning Action Plan and, alongside activities related to the Oil and Gas Authority’s Decommissioning and Supply Chain Strategies, is working collectively to ensure the approach to decommissioning harnesses opportunities for the UK supply chain.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-01-18T14:14:19.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671849/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671849/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671849/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-11","Fossil Fuels: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with the Scottish Government on the oil and gas decommissioning action plan, published by the Highlands and Islands Enterprise and Scottish Enterprise in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","59553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671850","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-19","<p>Questions 52386 and 52387 related to different subsets of arrears totals for 2015/16 – respectively these are:</p><p> </p><p>(a) £688,695 self-corrected arrears owed by employers found to be non-compliant with the national minimum wage but not issued with a Notice of Underpayment or financial penalty;</p><p>(b) £3,154,112 additional, self-corrected arrears owed by employers who were issued with a Notice of Underpayment and a penalty.</p><p> </p><p>The £4.6m figure for self-correction quoted in both the National Audit Office May 2016 report and the Low Pay Commission’s November 2016 report is another subset of 2015/16 arrears, given to the NAO before figures for 2015/16 were finalised. This includes the figures quoted above as well as:</p><p> </p><p>(a) £742,587 arrears voluntarily disclosed by employers who took part in HM Revenue and Custom’s 2015 National Minimum Wage campaign</p><p>(b) £3,560 arrears owed by employers who were issued with a Notice of Underpayment but no penalty.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-01-19T15:44:32.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671850/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671850/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671850/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-11","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answers of 15 November 2016 to Questions 52386 and 52387, and with reference to paragraph 1.8 of the National Audit Office report, Ensuring Employers Comply with National Minimum Wage Regulations, published in May 2016, and paragraph 5.191 of the Low Pay Commission's Autumn 2016 report, what the reasons are for the difference between the figure of £3.84 million given for the total sum of arrears identified through the self-correction mechanism in 2015-16 provided in those Answers and the figure of £4.6 million in those reports.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","59535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671851","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-17","<p>In 2015/16 we increased the National Minimum Wage (NMW) enforcement budget allocated to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) by £7m to £20m. These additional funds have allowed the recruitment of additional NMW compliance officers, so in addition to responding to every worker complaint, HMRC has been able to conduct more proactive, risked-based investigations into sectors where workers are more at risk of being underpaid.</p><p> </p><p>The increasing numbers of successful cases closed by HMRC show that our continued investment in minimum wage enforcement has had a real and positive impact on the lives of some of our most vulnerable workers.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-01-17T14:37:11.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671851/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671851/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671851/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-11","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Answer of 4 May 2016 to Question 36447 and pursuant to the Answers of 1 June 2016, corrected on 8 September, 7 October and 7 December 2016, to Questions 38139, 46899 and 56533, what the reasons are for the (a) increase in employer investigations resulting in the identification of minimum wage arrears from 964 in the whole of 2015-16 to 1,420 in the first half of 2016-17 and (b) apparent growth in the number of workers for whom arrears were recovered from 58,080 in 2015-16 to 48,154 in the first half of 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","59536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671853","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-18","<p>On 27 August 2015, a ‘Notice of intention to impose sanctions’ was issued to Home Energy and Lifestyle Management (HELMS). Having considered the representations received from HELMS and other affected persons, on 19 November 2015, my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State imposed a sanction on HELMS of a financial penalty of £10,500.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-01-18T14:12:42.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671853/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671853/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671853/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-11","Home Energy and Lifestyle Management: Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 11 January 2017 to Question 58548, what sanctions were imposed on Home Energy and Lifestyle Management Ltd for breaches of the Green Deal Code of Practice.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","59617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671854","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Stakeholder Working Group on EU Exit, Universities, Research and Innovation had its first meeting on 14 December 2016. Membership of the Group includes representatives from Higher Education, Research and Innovation funders, National Academies, Learned Societies and Business. The full membership and the terms of reference will be published in due course.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-01-16T09:24:28.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671854/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671854/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671854/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-11","EU Exit, Universities, Research and Innovation Stakeholder Working Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the terms of reference are of the Forum on EU Exit, Universities, Research and Innovation; who the members of that forum are; when that forum plans to meet; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","59635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671855","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Government is determined that everyone who is entitled to the National Minimum Wage (NMW) and National Living Wage (NLW) receives it. Anyone who feels they have been underpaid NMW or NLW should contact the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) reviews all complaints that are referred to them. Additionally, HMRC collates and analyses data from various sources in order to identify those employers who are potentially more likely to be underpaying NMW or NLW so that they can undertake targeted enforcement against those employers.</p><p> </p><p>For reasons of confidentiality, HMRC does not divulge information relating to the affairs of an individual or company or confirm whether or not there is an ongoing enquiry. HMRC investigates all cases where it is believed an employer is not paying its workers the minimum wage to ensure those workers receive what they are owed under the law.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-01-16T16:07:39.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671855/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671855/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671855/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-11","Minimum Wage: MITIE Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what investigations (a) have been concluded and (b) remain ongoing for alleged non-payment of the minimum wage by Mitie Group companies in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","59680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671856","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-16","<p>I refer the hon Member for Ochil and South Perthshire to the answer I gave to the hon Member for East Ham today, UIN: 59624.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-01-16T15:55:10.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671856/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671856/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671856/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-11","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what estimate his Department has made of the level of inward investment in the UK in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","59679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671857","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-16","<p>Ministers and officials in the Department for International Trade are working closely with counterparts across a wide range of countries and markets, in order to promote the UK as a great place to do business and with which to trade. The UK remains committed to pursuing free trade. That includes seeking to achieve continuity in our trade and investment relationships with third countries, including those covered by EU free trade agreements or other EU preferential arrangements.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-01-16T15:42:24.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671857/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671857/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671857/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-11","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what discussions he has had with his international counterparts on whether the UK will remain party to bilateral trade deals the EU currently has with other countries after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","59640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671858","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-16","<p>The Department for International Trade collects and validates information on known foreign direct investment (FDI) projects that materialise in the UK during a financial year. The results are published annually to allow for full quality control of the results, and can be found on Gov.uk.</p><p>The latest set of FDI results can be found using the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dit-inward-investment-results-for-the-tax-year-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dit-inward-investment-results-for-the-tax-year-2015-to-2016</a></p><p>An overview of the last five years worth of FDI into the UK regions can be accessed on:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/foreign-direct-investment-projects-by-ukti-regions-201011-to-201415" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/foreign-direct-investment-projects-by-ukti-regions-201011-to-201415</a></p><p>For any FDI and Export related publications, please consult:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/policies/exports-and-inward-investment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/policies/exports-and-inward-investment</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-01-16T15:48:21.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671858/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671858/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/671858/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-11","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 9 January 2017 to Question 58220, how many Foreign Direct Investment projects there have been into the UK since 23 June 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen 