"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670717","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-24","<p>The requested information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is aware that the cost of a child’s funeral is of considerable concern to parents at a very difficult time. I will shortly be meeting with the Honourable Member for Swansea East to discuss these issues further.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-01-24T11:31:27.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670717/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670717/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670717/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-01-10","Local Government: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many local authorities in England waive fees for children under the age of 17.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","59434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670718","Home Office","false","2017-01-13","<p>There is no question that fire and rescue services still have the resources they need to do their important work. In 2016/17 Merseyside Fire and Rescue Authority has £60.9m of core spending power, a reduction of 1 percent when compared to 2015/16. Since 2010/11, Merseyside Fire and Rescue Authorities’ non-ringfenced reserves rose by 124% to £28.2 million. Over the same period, the service attended 32 percent fewer incidents (including rescues and other non-fire incidents) and 33 percent fewer fires.</p><p>Fire and Rescue Authorities have delivered significant savings over the past five years but like all parts of the public sector, services need to increase efficiency and the Government believes there is scope to make further savings, for example through smarter working, greater collaboration and more effective procurement.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-13T10:07:24.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670718/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670718/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670718/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-10","Merseyside Fire and Rescue Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of funding changes on the service provided by Merseyside Fire and Rescue Service in the last six years.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","59428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670719","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-17","<p>The Department does not assess the extent to which individual members of the public rent out their driveways. The Department has given local authorities the tools through the planning system to take action if there are significant planning concerns such as public nuisance to the local residents and community.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-01-17T17:37:03.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670719/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670719/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670719/answer","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670719/answer/previousversion/29862","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-10","Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the (a) prevalence and (b) environmental and social impact of residents making their private parking spaces available for hire; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","59487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670720","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>The UK tourism industry is flourishing and we are determined to help to maintain and grow its success. We have made clear that we will pursue the right outcome that works for the unique circumstances of the UK. The Department is committed to working with the UK tourism industry to ensure that its needs and views are understood and considered as the UK develops its negotiating position. The Secretary of State and the Minister for Sport, Tourism &amp; Heritage are both holding roundtable meetings in January with the tourism industry.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-01-13T13:48:05.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670720/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670720/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670720/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Tourism: UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent assessment she has made of the importance of the Customs Union to the UK's tourism industry.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","59462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670721","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>Until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the European Union and all the rights and obligations of EU membership, including the European Health Insurance Card (EHIC), remain in force. The outcome of negotiations will determine what arrangements apply once the UK has left the EU, and the Government is working to ensure the best possible outcome for the British people.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-01-13T13:48:59.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670721/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670721/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670721/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Medical Treatments Abroad: Europe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent steps she has taken to ensure the UK's continued participation in the European Health Insurance Card scheme after the UK exits the EU.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","59463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670722","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>UK residents spent £39.0 billion overseas in 2015, on 65.7 million visits. This is a 9.8 per cent increase in spend, and a 9.4 per cent increase in the number of visits, when compared to 2014. No assessment has been made on the contribution of outbound tour operators to the UK economy.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-01-13T13:50:03.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670722/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670722/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670722/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent assessment she has made of the value to the UK economy of the outbound tourism industry.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","59464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670723","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>Officials are working closely with the tourism industry on this issue. EU nationals make 9% of the UK’s tourism workforce and make a valuable contribution to its success. We want to make the most of their skills and experience; working with the tourism industry to provide training opportunities and work places for the best workforce possible.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-01-13T13:51:29.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670723/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670723/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670723/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Tourism: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent assessment she has made of the importance of continued access to the EU employment market to the UK's tourism industry.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","59481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670724","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>Consecutive, independent evaluations have demonstrated the positive impacts that National Citizen Service (NCS) delivers to both its participants and their communities. NCS is delivering more confident, capable and engaged young people. Previous evaluations for NCS are available at:<a href="http://www.ncsyes.co.uk/our-story" target="_blank"> www.ncsyes.co.uk/our-story</a></p><p> </p><p>Work is ongoing on the 2015 evaluation and we plan to publish it in the near future.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-01-13T11:38:31.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670724/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670724/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670724/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Voluntary Work: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she expects the National Citizen Service 2015 Evaluation report to be published.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","59441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670725","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-16","<p>I refer the Hon Member to the written statement made by my Right Hon. Friend, the Secretary of State on 1.0 January 2018, Vol 619 Col 8WS.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-16T16:52:26.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670725/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670725/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","21st Century Fox: Sky","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to her Written Statement of 10 January 2017, what steps she plans to take to invite public representations to her Department on public interest considerations as set out in the Enterprise Act 2002 on the proposed merger of 21st Century Fox and Sky.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","59468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670726","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>Since June 2016, both Ministers and officials have held a number of meetings, with industry bodies and representatives and others to understand the issues and concerns that face broadcasters prior to the triggering of Article 50.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-13T09:49:01.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670726/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670726/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Broadcasting: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps the Government is taking to protect jobs in the commercial broadcasting industry prior to the triggering of Article 50.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","59469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670727","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>There have been no discussions between the Secretary and State and Ofcom on consumers' ability to transfer their email archive when they change service provider. Ofcom do not have regulatory responsibility for the providers of such services, or powers to intervene.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-13T09:47:09.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670727/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670727/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Internet Service Providers: Email","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with Ofcom on consumers' ability to transfer their email archive when they change service provider.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","59400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670728","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Government intends to introduce the replacement for the current Horserace Betting Levy in April 2017. We will make a further announcement shortly.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-01-13T13:54:42.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670728/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670728/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670728/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Horse Racing: Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to make a decision on new funding arrangements for the Horse Race Betting Levy.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","59408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670729","Home Office","false","2017-01-18","<p>In delivering the Emergency Services Network (ESN), the mobile network operator EE will deliver up to 291 new mast sites. Government will deliver approximately 230 further sites (known as the “Extended Area Services” (EAS) sites) in the most remote and rural areas of Great Britain.</p><p>EE has indicated that they aim to provide commercial services from all the new sites that they are building for ESN and the EAS sites although this may be dependent on the backhaul technologies used at sites to connect the site to EE’s telecommunications system.</p><p>Under the terms of the State Aid decision for ESN, any ESN site where EE offers a commercial service must be made available to the other UK mobile operators and interested parties to provide their own a service on an equal and non-discriminatory basis</p><p>For EAS sites, the principal objective is to provide coverage to meet the needs of the emergency services, but the Home Office is working with the Welsh Government, Scottish Government and DCMS to identify any proposed mast locations which could improve mobile coverage in future, with a view to ensuring these are built to a specification which could accommodate multiple operators.</p><p>No new masts are planned for the purposes of ESN in the Rhondda constituency, because EE have confirmed that their existing site network will provide the coverage required.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","59353","2017-01-18T17:28:19.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670729/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670729/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670729/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-10","Aerials: Rhondda","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Emergency Services Network masts there are planned to be in the Rhondda.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","59374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670730","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-18","<p>Data on the proportion of the population of the Rhondda that has (a) 2G, (b) 3G and (c) 4G is not held centrally. Ofcom have published data at the local authority level on the percentage of premises where there is likely to be a 4G signal from all four operators. They will be publishing similar data for 2G and 3G shortly.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-18T17:34:04.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670730/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670730/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670730/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Mobile Phones: Rhondda","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of the population of the Rhondda has (a) 2G, (b) 3G and (c) 4G mobile coverage.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","59352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670731","Home Office","false","2017-01-18","<p>In delivering the Emergency Services Network (ESN), the mobile network operator EE will deliver up to 291 new mast sites. Government will deliver approximately 230 further sites (known as the “Extended Area Services” (EAS) sites) in the most remote and rural areas of Great Britain.</p><p>EE has indicated that they aim to provide commercial services from all the new sites that they are building for ESN and the EAS sites although this may be dependent on the backhaul technologies used at sites to connect the site to EE’s telecommunications system.</p><p>Under the terms of the State Aid decision for ESN, any ESN site where EE offers a commercial service must be made available to the other UK mobile operators and interested parties to provide their own a service on an equal and non-discriminatory basis</p><p>For EAS sites, the principal objective is to provide coverage to meet the needs of the emergency services, but the Home Office is working with the Welsh Government, Scottish Government and DCMS to identify any proposed mast locations which could improve mobile coverage in future, with a view to ensuring these are built to a specification which could accommodate multiple operators.</p><p>No new masts are planned for the purposes of ESN in the Rhondda constituency, because EE have confirmed that their existing site network will provide the coverage required.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","59374","2017-01-18T17:28:19.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670731/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670731/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670731/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-10","Emergency Services Network: Aerials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will take steps to ensure that all four mobile network operators are available on a