"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670732","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-26","The Department for Culture, Media and Sport monitors proposed changes to library service provision throughout England, however the Department does not hold complete figures on total public library closures since February 2016.","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-01-26T10:05:07.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670732/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670732/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670732/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-10","Public Libraries: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many public libraries have closed since February 2016.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","59269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670733","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-01-13","As this programme is in its early stages, no assessment has yet been made, but its impact will be evaluated during and after execution to ensure impact and value for money. The British Council manages the allocation of our funding for grassroots football in China, which aims to position the UK as China's priority partner for sport.","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-01-13T14:53:51.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670733/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670733/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670733/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-10","China: Football","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the outcome of the £3 million funding for a grassroots football programme in China announced by the Chancellor of the Exchequer on 23 September 2015.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","59261"
