"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670742","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-13","<p>While we are working to produce an updated version of JSP900 which is releasable to 5-eyes and NATO allies, it is now not the case that we are producing a version which would be releasable to all. It is judged that the necessary removal of information that would prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces would result in a version with insufficient detail to warrant publication.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-13T14:13:37.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670742/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670742/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670742/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-10","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 25 February 2016 to Question 27212, if he will release a releasable version of the JSP 900 UK Targeting Policy.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","59422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670743","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no direct contracts with AEI Cables, however, the company is a subcontractor on some defence programmes, including the Queen Elizabeth Class Carriers and Type 45 destroyers. Our prime contractors are responsible for managing their supply chains and, as such, following the closure of any company, we would expect them to take any appropriate action to ensure continuity of supply and to make decisions about future suppliers.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","59457 ; 59458 ; 59459 ; 59460","2017-01-13T14:08:12.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670743/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670743/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670743/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-10","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, where existing contracts between his Department and AEI Cables are in place, whether his Department and defence programme main contractors have identified UK-based suppliers for future UK defence programme cabling requirements.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","59470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670744","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment has a regimental headquarters and three battalions, two Regular (1st Battalion The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment and 2nd Battalion The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment) and one Reserve (4th Battalion The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment).</p><p>The regimental headquarters is based in Fulwood Barracks, Preston, which is planned for disposal under the Better Defence Estate Strategy in 2022. A future location for the regimental headquarters will be determined following a process of detailed assessment and planning.</p><p>The 1st Battalion will remain a Light Infantry battalion. It is currently planned that its regular liability will grow from around 560 to 630 by 2025. On return from Cyprus in 2018, it will be based in Dale Barracks, Chester before, on current plans rotating back to Cyprus in 2022.</p><p>As announced by written ministerial statement on 15 December 2016 (HCWS367), The 2nd Battalion will be assigned to the Army's new Specialist Infantry role and joins the Headquarters Specialist Infantry Group in 2019. Under current plans its liability will change from around 560 to 270, with the balance being reinvested in other areas. It will be based in Aldershot, from 2020.</p><p>The 4th Battalion will remain a Reserve Light Infantry battalion with its headquarters in Preston and other companies in Liverpool, Blackburn, Carlisle and Manchester. It is currently planned to grow this Reserve liability from around 400 to 500 by 2025.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-13T14:13:04.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670744/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670744/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670744/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-10","Duke of Lancaster's Regiment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his policy is on the future strength, structure and basing of the Duke of Lancaster's Regiment.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","59473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670745","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-13","<p>Pursuant to my previous answer, since 20 September 2016 UK Reapers continue to operate in support of Operation SHADER in Iraq and Syria on intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance sorties.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-13T14:14:54.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670745/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670745/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-10","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 12 October 2016 to Question 46487, to which countries RAF Reaper drones have been deployed on intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance sorties since 20 September 2016.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","59496"
